node.text:
"Almost every family in America faces a mental health challenge at some point, and my family is no exception. We must remove the stigma and continue to educate ourselves so that we see the signs when someone is struggling and are empowered to offer support. And we can and will save lives by doing so.” - Kendra Scott

Go behind the design with our VP of Creative Design, Leah Lucas, to learn more about the inspiration for our Sun & Moon Charm, benefiting mental health causes. ☀️🌙✨

node.title: Behind the Design of Our Charm Benefiting Mental Health Causes ☀️🌙✨

Wear Life Beautifully. #WearItLikeAMom

node.text:
We are so proud to celebrate Meghan, The Duchess of Sussex, and join the #40x40 campaign by donating 40 minutes of service in honor of her 40th birthday. Today, we will be using that time to support @onoursleevesofficial, the national movement to break stigmas around children’s mental health. By helping get free mental health resources into one million classrooms across America, we’re empowering teachers to be more equipped in having these crucial conversations with their students. 

Will you join us in donating 40 minutes of your time today to support children’s mental health? This work is more critical than ever and by nominating a teacher for the Million Classroom Project, every minute of good we create will have an even larger impact. 

Happy birthday to you, Meghan! I can’t think of a better way to celebrate. - Kendra

#CompassionInAction #OnOurSleeves
